                <h2>Rotation</h2>
                <ol class="rotation-steps">
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Activate all shouts before combat</strong> &mdash; War Cry, Rallying Cry, and Challenging Shout. This gives you full offensive and defensive buffs before engaging packs.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Ground Stomp to stun and apply Vulnerable</strong> &mdash; Use Ground Stomp on packs and elites to apply a group-wide stun and Vulnerable. This sets up the window for massive Bash damage.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Spam Bash constantly</strong> &mdash; Your primary action. Bash generates Fury, deals massive damage, and has a chance to stun on every hit. Focus on elites and bosses for maximum effectiveness.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Paingorger's extends stun duration</strong> &mdash; Every Bash hit extends the duration of your stuns. Keep hitting stunned enemies to maintain permanent stun lock throughout the fight.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Recast shouts on cooldown</strong> &mdash; Keep War Cry, Rallying Cry, and Challenging Shout up at all times. Rage of Harrogath reduces their cooldowns for near-permanent uptime.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Pop Wrath of the Berserker for burst windows</strong> &mdash; Use your Ultimate during dangerous elite encounters or boss fights for a massive damage boost and Unstoppable to break CC.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Maintain full Fury for Battle Trance</strong> &mdash; Bash generates Fury constantly. Stay at maximum Fury to keep Battle Trance's damage multiplier active at all times.</p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
